  <text>
    <body>
      <ab type="lido:objectWorkType">Leaflet</ab>
      <ab subtype="creation" type="lido:event">
        <date>1943 after</date>
      </ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">The frameless leaflet features a photograph of a couple. She is looking at him; he is looking towards the camera. Their hands are clutched at breast height. She has fair hair and her light-coloured dress is strapless. His hair and moustache are black, his shirt white. He is wearing a necktie with red and black stripes. He is older than she is. In the lower part of the image, the film title is printed in Cyrillic and Latin in a red field.</ab>
      <ab subtype="comment" type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">Ferdinand Marian and Winnie Markus played the leading roles. The film was directed by Viktor Tourjansky and released in 1943.</ab>
